%N A088588 a(0)=1, a(n) = floor(Pi * exp(f(n)*(f(n)+1)/2) * prime(n/2)#) where f(n)=floor((n+1)/2) and p(n)# is the n-th primorial.
%C A088588 Essentially a duplicate of A088589. - _Sean A. Irvine_, Apr 28 2026
%t A088588 Table[If[n==0, 1, Floor[Pi*Exp[Sum[j, {j, 0, Floor[(n+1)/2]}]]*Product[Prime[i], {i, 1, Floor[n/2]}]]], {n, 0, 20}]
